The battle against the Rot has left Buddy’s family in ruins, and now they must withstand another force trying to subvert him: his own celebrity!

Continued from Animal Man #6

Buddy Baker watches his movie "Tights". The movie picks up where Cliff stopped watching in Issue 6.

Chaz Grant gets out of the hospital after getting beaten up dressed as The Red Thunder, and to his surprise his ex-wife, Paige and there son Jamie are there to pick him up and take him home. There, in his messy studio apartment he is visited by a talent agent named Tom Drummond, who wants to represent Chaz.

Chaz thinks it over and agrees. He is then launched into a whirl wind of talk shows, endorsement deal and staged outings with celebrity starlets. Everything seems to be going well until he is at a party and is approached by Paige. Chaz still loves his ex-wife but she has moved on and breaks his heart again. While Chaz is leaving the party he hears a cry for help and saves a woman from being raped by a well dressed man.

The man is the studio CEO and files charges against Chaz, this leads to Chaz being dropped by Drummond, and ending his career. Whats worst Dummond owns the Red Thunder brand and Chaz can never dress up like the hero again.

Weeks later, Chaz is missing and presumed dead, but Jamie catches a piece on the news about how a masked man rescued some children from a house fire. Jamie knows his father is alive and still doing good deeds.

Buddy Baker turns off the movie looks a picture of Cliff and cries. Then the phone rings, it is Rodger, Buddy's agent. He tells Buddy he has been nominated for a academy award for best actor for Tights.
2013-04-29|2013-05-05.name: Tights, Part Two

This is perhaps the mightiest issue of Comic Heroes of them all! We look at Marvel's biggest hitter, the Norse Thunder God THOR, including a complete hero history of the character - and how his early issues defined modern comic book storytelling!

We talk to Al Ewing about making a splash at Marvel on Mighty Avengers; Brian Michael Bendis about the new X-Men crossover, Battle of the Atom; David Lloyd about the legacy of V For Vendetta and the digital future of comics; and creator James O'Barr about his return to The Crow.

2013-10-07|2013-10-13.description:
This 20th volume is particularly dense with romantic intrigue, as Marcie and Charlie Brown end up at camp together, sending Peppermint Patty into mad jealousy (especially since Marcie can't resist teasing her)... and an old friend of Charlie Brown's attempts to look him up again but confuses him with Snoopy and goes on a date with him instead.

But the most crucial event in romance is Charlie Brown's romance with Peggy Jean — even though he's so flustered in his first conversation with her that he ends up stuck with the name "Brownie Charles" for the duration of her relationship ("I kind of like it...").

This volume also introduces yet another Snoopy sibling, Olaf, who is humiliatingly invited to enter an ugly-dog contest (and, even more humiliatingly, wins). Plus lots of Zen-like Spike-and-cactus strips, Sally Brown non sequiturs, D-minuses for Peppermint Patty, and wise thoughts from Franklin's grandpa... Snoopy treks through the wilderness as the Beagle Scoutmaster and through the desert as the World Famous Sergeant of the Foreign Legion, Woodstock takes a whack at being the King of the Jungle, Lucy enjoys Michael Jackson on her boom box, Marcie's perfectionism leads to a crack-up, Pigpen runs for class president, Snoopy gets called to jury duty... and for a change, Lucy pulls the football out from under Charlie Brown.

Rachel and Jet must face off against Mary Scott and Hannah the snake lady if they intend to save the town of Manson, and witchcraft is the weapon of choice. Is Rachel ready for such a dangerous test of her long-forgotten powers? Find out in the latest issue of Terry Moore's horror thriller!

volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

Welcome to House of M, a world, where mutants and humans live together in peace and every hero's deepest desires come true. However the beauty of this Utopia is only skin-deep, it's everything else than a paradise. As the reality slowly begins to crystallize itself, in the midst of the growing chaos only one thing is for sure: The Marvel-Universe will never be how it was!

Collects House of M #1 - 8

From the fallout of NECESSARY EVIL, comes new beginnings and new twists that will be felt in the pages of Spider-Man for years to come! SUPERIOR SPIDER-MAN #20 is where it all starts! Do NOT miss this one!

It's the first ever adventure for the Superior Spider-Man and the Black Cat. Felicia Hardy always cared for the Spider more than the man. But what happens when that man is Otto Octavius?

Plus: A day Otto has been waiting for is finally here. Is the world ready for "Dr. Peter Parker"... and what he plans to do next?

Evil Inc Monthly is a pre-release of all of the Evil Inc strips scheduled for the upcoming month -- plus a special bonus feature created from the archive of the comic. Evil Inc is a corporation run for super-villains by super-villains.

The November Evil Inc comic is 30 pages, and it kicks off a storyline that includes a cameo appearance by Walter White, the return of the Spoiler, and … a surprise wedding proposal!

Then… in the bonus feature, Tales from the Evil Inc Archive, Dr. Muskiday — with an assist by Phenomenal Lass – invents a device that puts his brain in control of Captain Heroic’s body. So what happens when Amazing Amazon puts the moves on Our Hero?

X-O Manowar finally has it all, and his people finally have a land they can call home…but threats from all sides now threaten to destroy Aric and the peace he has struggled to secure.
